      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to see how they beat superstar trotter KEAYANG ZAHARA (1) from the ace draw. She continued on her winning way with another Group 1 success last start, working to the front from a couple of spots wider before taking out the Great Southern Star by close to 9m. She is 12 from 12 here and unbeaten at the distance. Expect her to keep those perfect records intact. JILLIBY DREAMLOVER (3) has ground to make up on KEAYANG ZAHARA through the Great Southern Star but she was brave in boxing on to place. Has been progressing strongly this campaign, winning six of her previous seven starts. Could be the bridesmaid again. LOVEMETO NZ (2) will enjoy the better barrier having come from the back row in both rounds of the Great Southern Star, finishing 5m behind JILLIBY DREAMLOVER in the heats before he was down the track in the final. Could be more competitive from this draw. EL RESAMO (6) has plenty of ground to make up on Keayang Zahara through last start but his prior efforts were sound. Include.",
